derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English : from Middle Low German and Middle Dutch bolwerk; related to bole and work

entry.def: A bulwark against something protects you against it. A bulwark of something protects it.

example.ex: The abbeys were founded in the 12th century by King David as a bulwark against the English...
example.tran: 这些修道院是12世纪大卫王用来抵御英国人而修建的堡垒。

example.ex: The House of Lords is the only bulwark of democracy in this country.
example.tran: 在这个国家，上议院是唯一的民主堡垒。
